mage" (since it only checks length for text). But `@IsMessageContent()` doesn\'t
have `@IsOptional()` semantics, so if content is missing/null, `typeof value !==
"string"` returns false, failing validation.\n\nActually wait, looking at `SendM
essageDto`:\n```typescript\n@IsMessageContent()\ncontent!: string;\n```\n\nThere
\'s no `@IsOptional()`. So content is always required. But the `IsMessageContent
` validator says:\n```typescript\nvalidate(value: unknown, args: ValidationArgum
ents) {\n  if (typeof value !== "string") {\n    return false;\n  }\n  ...\n}\n`
``\n\nSo if content is missing, it returns false. This means image messages MUST
have content. The review says:\n"问题: content 字段有 @IsString()（未加 @IsOptio
nal()），同时 @ValidateIf 仅作用于 @MaxLength。因此当 type = "image" 时，若 cont
ent 为空或缺失，ValidationPipe 会在 Controller 层拦截请求，返回 400。"\n\nBut in
the current code, `@IsMessageContent()` replaces `@IsString()` and `@MaxLength()
`. However, `@IsMessageContent()` is still applied unconditionally and requires 
content to be a string. So image messages without content would still fail at th
e DTO validation level, even though `im.service.ts` has a check for image conten
t.\n\nWait, but the service.ts check happens AFTER DTO validation. If DTO valida
tion rejects empty content for image messages, the request never reaches the ser
vice. So this is still a bug!\n\nI should fix the DTO to make content optional, 
and rely on the service-level validation. Or make the custom validator handle mi
ssing values for image types.\n\n10. message:delivered timing - Looking at im.ga
teway.ts lines 87-96:\n```typescript\nconst receiverSockets = await this.server\
n  .in(`user:${result.receiverId}`)\n  .fetchSockets();\nif (receiverSockets.len
gth > 0) {\n  client.emit("message:delivered", ...);\n}\n```\nThis only emits de
livered if receiver is online. This is better than before but still not perfect.
The review wanted it to be after the receiver actually receives it. But this is 
a major issue, not blocking.\n\n11. Real-time conversation list update - Looking
at conversation_list_page.dart lines 41-56, there\'s a `BlocListener<ImBloc, ImS
tate>` that listens to `ConversationListNeedsRefresh` and refreshes the cubit. A
nd im_bloc.dart `_onConversationUpdated` emits `ConversationListNeedsRefresh`. S
o this is fixed! ✅\n\n12. SwChatInputBar Semantics container:true - ✅ Fixed (l
ine 113 has `container: true`)\n\nSo the remaining issues I can see:\n1. **SendM
essageDto.content** is required for all messages including images (Major #9 from
Review 2)\n2. **BDD tests** might still have empty implementations (Major #7, #8
from Review 2, Major #9 from Review 1)\n\nLet me check the BDD test files quickl
y.',
    encrypted=None
)
